caption: Had a taste for some Mexican food, went to this Place and stood at the front for a few minutes. A guy comes to greet us and then walks away. Lol. They only had 2 people working the floor, so no big deal. But the service after that was pretty awkward. We got a lot of stares from workers and locals which made me slightly uncomfortable but I didn’t make a big deal about it. The quesadillas were great. But we should’ve just stuck with the Mexican options. My boyfriend ordered hot wings and we got the wrong order so we had to wait another 30 minutes for soggy, cold wings. I’ll consider giving it another try when I have a taste for authentic Mexican. Hopefully our experience is less awks. Lol

Egg-based breakfasts are not bad; skip the pancake offerings, which are poor.  Regular Mexican entrees are okay. Nice service, but a bit over-priced for the actual quality of food. Free parking, though, and it's ample.  2 1/2 stars, really.
My wife and i go here every weekend on date nights for 7 years and it's better each time. This is truly a Chicago must go to place for the best food and atmosphere around.
Foods great!
After a long day of hiking, we ended up here and so we were hungry by the time we arrived. The restaurant was busy, but that was a sign that the food was fine, so we were not discouraged.
This Mexican Restaurant was recommended to us by our hotel as an authentic Mexican restaurant. Great, enjoyable atmosphere in an old-fashioned setting.
Love this place. Awesome customer service.

Excellent restaurant for Mexican food. The restaurant is beautiful... full of color and authentic Mexican decor. The food is delicious. Many choices on their new menu, including breakfast options. Everyone there is really friendly. We can't wait to go back! 😁
The staff is super friendly and the food is super rich in flavors and tasty.

Best quarantine meal I’ve ever had ! This is some top class Mexican cuisine eating! The most thoughtfully packed take out I’ve ever had literally the presentation was beautiful as if I was sitting right there at the restaurant itself Definitely gave me dine in vibes very tasty and very appealing it’s a win win! Gotta try that Tres Leches Yum 🤤
Favorite place close by for a quick bite
Quality Mexican!

Food:  ⭐ ⭐ ⭐ ⭐ Ambiance: ⭐ ⭐ ⭐ ⭐ Service: ⭐ ⭐ ⭐ Drinks: ⭐ The food here is absolutely delicious. I ordered the shrimp tacos (tacos camarones) and I kid you not, I could taste the fresh char on the shrimp,  the taste you only get from grilling in the summer you know.  The salsa was actually somewhat spicyand the chips were warm. Hallelujah. 🙌 The only con was their margaritas are trash. I ordered the classic and it legit taste like salt then I ordered the peach and it legit tasted like sugar. Just get straight shots if you want to drink.
Authentic Mexican Cuisine, Excellent Margaritas & Artistic Atmosphere. What's not to love?

Food is amazing! I had their steak burrito and it was one of the best I have had. The reason I gave it 4 stars is because 16$ is quite expensive for a burrito. This will make me not come back as often as I would like to. I wish they were priced more appropriate.

We were at the this restaurant Edgewater Mexican Cafe on Tuesday 10-13-20 for what had been before for the advertised dollar  taco 🌮 Tuesday indoor dinning only. We ordered and the waiter was impatient with our questions regarding our questions as my mother has an allergic reactions to sunflower oil. The was more impatient with the question about the Dollar Taco Tuesday question. Although he said special price for Tuesday’s was not available we were hungry & we order and ate. The carne asada tacos were dry and tasteless. The guacamole which we had before was half the portion as before and also tasteless. Perhaps because of the location they are not serving the dishes as before with less spices. The only reasonable tasty item was the red salsa. With that said the place cannot survive on just salsa! Thumbs down very dark atmosphere only three tables occupied indoors and two tables outdoors and two people at the bar. BTW I just finished speaking with the owner Daniel regarding eating on Dollar Taco Tuesday and Daniel said in two years he never had such a promotion and It’s an insult to think he would ever do so. I’ve been a residential owner in the past 30yrs. I’m familiar with many of our local restaurants. It’s insulting for this restaurant to have such poor quality food and client service.

What a great neighborhood spot! I love dining on the outdoor patio (which is on Winthrop, not busy Bryn Mawr). Their portions are quite generous. I ordered a two-veggie tamale dinner for take-out and it came with massive tamales, two boxes of rice and beans, container cups of salsa (3x) and mole sauce, and a bag of tortilla chips. $14 for tamales seem a little high but for the amount of food and quality you get, it's absolutely worth it.
The langostinos were fire! 🔥

Me and my husband enjoyed a nice cold beer.
I love the outdoor seating and also their guacamole

Great spot for dinner and drinks. We sat on the patio and the service was good. I loved the guacamole and frozen margarita, always makes me feel like I’m on vacation. The food was good too, lots of vegetarian options. #vegetarian #casual #mexican #outdoordining

I love this place.  The food is delicious (everything is made in house).  Their mole is wonderful, best I've had.  Lovely staff.  Highly recommended.

We had beef, steak, and fish tacos. All delicious. Chimichanga and scallops were wonderful. Free parking behind restaurant.

Generally the food is good, but occasionally you go in for a particular item, and it's made totally different.  Can be very disappointing. But over all, I like the restaurant and go 2-3 times a month.

Staff is really pleasant. Added mole to my burrito and was amazing. The margarita and flan were nice.

We love edgewater Mexican café , We can come here all the time.  The staff is always great and friendly, and they are extremely pet friendly (patio seating)  The food is really good, I personally like the poblano soup and the steak tacos.  my boyfriend always gets the burrito. Love love love

This is my favorite Mexican restaurant! I get the same thing every time i go; Carne Asada Taco dinner (3 tacos with rice & beans) and a small pitcher of the House Margarita *skinny*..  Order that and I promise you will be back!  The service is great. Staff is friendly and knowledgeable.  Highly recommend

They serve chips with salsa at the table before your food comes. I love the chips they are a little thick, which is good I hate it when chips break really easily. The salsa is thin, more liquidy...and it's spicy! I also really like to have the chips with the beans and rice that is served with the enchiladas. SO GOOD!

I've literally been coming back to this restaurant for 1 year now, wow I'm getting old...  The food still tastes great, portion sizes are the same (huge). And, more recently I've switched from lime margaritas on the rocks to the frozen strawberry and it's next level.  I still always get the same dish, enchiladas rojas with a side of guac. I literally have never had anything else here, but my friends and family have and no one has ever had a bad meal.  Outdoor seating in the summer is an extra bonus.
great food!!!!!

VERY mediocre; especially for the price. Edgewater is not the place for Mexican food. This place is very overpriced and the food is typically overcooked and bland. The drinks are decent, but living in Logan, I don't feel comfortable paying so much for such an uninteresting meal.

A great place to dine indoors or outdoors during warm weather. I have been going to this restaurant since 2010 and am always pleased with the service, the food and the drinks. Keep up the good work.

Horrible horrible horrible customer service from Ruben(the owner). I normally come a few times a week for drinks but today will be my last. My mom ordered me a jack and coke a regular which is what I always get. But Ruben decided to do a tall to do a price hike. As a former bartender I know the game all to well. So I explained to him the difference and he gets a attitude and tells me so what in a very disrespectful tone. So he takes the drink and gives to his friend. And pours me a shot with coke and now charge me $10 plus a $.50 for coke. What a joke and rip off when I was just here Monday got the same order for $7.50 which is what I normally pay. Never again and I can't wait to discuss this on my radio show. BEWARE OF FRAUDULENT ACTIVITY WITH THE OWNER RUBEN!!!

Pretty poor service We stopped eating here a couple years ago because the service was always slow and the table side guacamole was NOT take side. My husband noticed a sign, under new management. We decided to give it another chance. Same problems. Slow service. Guacamole not take side even though we're paid 10 bucks for it. Aand ur wasn't very good. The pork was very gristley.  The cream of pablano soup was good though

Come at 4-7pm on Mondays to Wednesdays when they have Margarita Mondays, Happy Hour & Taco Tuesdays with $2.50 tacos & $6 margaritas, and Wine Wednesdays with $6 wine glasses! Cheers! Their tacos & margaritas are awesome!!!
Very tasty food. Great margaritas. Only $6 on Mondays. Nice atmosphere and friendly service.
Great food. Even though the previous Mexican Cafe was good, the new version has improved food. Very good.

While there are many words I could use to describe the Edgewater Mexican Cafe, I’m going to say only this: Edgewater Mexican Cafe is a bad restaurant... should've known by the fact that they're still using part of the old "That Little Mexican Cafe" sign. They simply removed "That Little". All you need to know is the service is really slow, food is bland and it's overpriced for the quality. Go elsewhere or eat at home.
Great place,  great drinks and environment

I ended up at this place spontaneously last week and it was absolutely amazing. The waiter gave us free salsa and corns chips and refills as we were looking over the menu and while waiting for the food. The food was very flavourful, a great portion size and tasted AMAZING. The service was great as well and our waiter was very attentive/accommodating; allowing us to customize and letting us choose from the dinner menu, although it was lunch. If I lived in the area, i would've been a frequent customer.
Friendly atmosphere A lot of street parking Excellent food
Margaritas are really good and a great value during happy hour.  Ordered a burrito with steak and it was huge and tasted great! Chips and salsa tasted fresh, will for sure be back.
The people there were very friendly. The bar was great. Food was hot. The owner was very nice. The waitress was great also.

Very good food, a little bit on the high end for a taqueria.

This is definitely the best Mexican food restaurant that I have tried in my life.  The melted chorizo ​​was super great, excellent service.  The bartender Mr. Daniel was very nice, very talkative, he prepares great margaritas. Highly recommended

Good food, strong drinks and low prices. Been here for taco Tuesday 3 weeks in a row 😎

Great!

Went there for brunch on Sunday with my two sisters. We had the buffet. A deal at $11.99. the food was very tasty. My favorite was the steak fajitas. The steak was truly some of the most tender meat I ever ate. We had tons of great food and prompt and friendly service. Do and enjoy!

This place is great for brunch, meeting friends for a drink, maybe even a date. The prices are reasonable and they have specials throughout the week. I enjoyed their Sunday buffet as you get to enjoy different dishes for a set price and that includes some desserts and a coffee or juice. You can’t really beat that! The staff is super friendly, although they seem a bit disorganized and nervous, which probably comes from being a new restaurant, so, be patient and kind. I gave them 3 stars because no restaurant, as Tex-Mex as it may be, should get away with serving basically Tostitos salsa! And I get it, some Americans aren’t into hot or spicy, but if you’re offering tacos al pastor or any kind for that matter, you better have a good salsa! At least options! Other than that, I recommend this restaurant and I’m very happy it’s part of our neighborhood.
So delicious and very nice staff!
New owners but same great food & cocktails
Best Mexican restaurant around Edgewater, maybe even Chicago! Service and food both were outstanding. Can’t wait to come back!
I really enjoyed the food and reasonably priced and the atmosphere was wonderful.

Excellent food, very friendly and attentive staff.  Free parking in the back of restaurant.  Reasonable food and beverage prices.  I highly recommend the Méxican Caffee!

Food was tasty, prices were reasonable, service was good, and setting is lovely.  So glad to have a good Mexican restaurant in the 'hood.  Support this new local business!
The carne asada meal was prepared exactly as ordered (well done but still very juicy) and steak tacos dinner was excellent.  Excellent food at very reasonable prices. Free parking in the back.

The carne asade with chimichurri sauce and the flan are amazing.  The staff is friendly and attentive. The "El Jefe" cocktail is just lovely.  The prices are perfect.  The Sunday brunch is also really good. I love this place.

the best roasted green sauce i have ever had. had to buy some to take with me. great layout on sunday brunch. nice upscale atmosphere. great place for large parties or to take a date. excellent bar selection if you enjoy good tequilas and margaritas. they also have good beer selections. i would definitely return to satisfy my cravings.
